page.title: 03Roads
page.content: The B1166 goes through Gedney Hill. It comes from Holbeach to Wisbech. The B1166 is the only road on the A.A. map that goes through Gedney Hill. There is a lot of information in the A.A. book of roads. When you go to Holbeach you can branch off and go to Whaplode Fen.The road also goes through Holbeach St. Johns. Here are some of the droves that had cattle down them: Dog Drove,Mole Drove, West Drove,Fen Drove,Cross Drove, French Drove,Chapel Drove and New Fen Drove.There are some lanes like Mill Lane,Highstock Lane and Long Lane. There are no speed restrictions in this area.
